<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,830,972]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
See 
<bibRefCitation author="Wesener, T. &amp; Wagele, J. - W." box="[200,510,830,856]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="1 - 85" refId="ref61546" refString="Wesener, T. &amp; Wagele, J. - W. (2008). The giant pill-millipedes of Madagascar: revision of the genus Zoosphaerium (Myriapoda, Diplopoda, Sphaerotheriida). Zoosystema, 30 (1), 1 - 85." type="journal article" year="2008">Wesener &amp; Wägele (2008)</bibRefCitation>
for an extensive revision of the genus. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1895" box="[966,1135,831,856]" class="Diplopoda" family="Arthrosphaeridae" genus="Zoosphaerium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sphaerotheriida" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[966,1135,831,856]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Zoosphaerium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was divided into speciesgroups, but it remains unclear if those species-groups represent monophyletic units which might deserve generic status. One new species-group, based on 
<taxonomicName authority="(de Saussure &amp; Zehntner, 1902)" baseAuthorityName="de Saussure &amp; Zehntner" baseAuthorityYear="1902" box="[743,1271,908,934]" class="Diplopoda" family="Arthrosphaeridae" genus="Zoosphaerium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sphaerotheriida" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="blandum">
<emphasis box="[743,878,908,933]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Z. blandum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="de Saussure, H. &amp; Zehntner, L." box="[897,1263,908,934]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="1 - 356" refId="ref60181" refString="de Saussure, H. &amp; Zehntner, L. (1902) Myriapodes de Madagascar, In: Grandidier (Ed.), Histoire physique, naturelle et politique de Madagascar. 27 (53), Alfred Grandidier, Paris, France, i - viii, pp. 1 - 356, plates 13 - 15." type="journal article" year="1902">de Saussure &amp; Zehntner, 1902</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is introduced here. Only two of the new species could not be assigned to a species-group.
</paragraph>
